il wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Coxe II was born in 1440, in Moulsford, Berkshire, England, his father, Thomas Coxe I, was 40 and his mother, Mrs. Coxe, was 35. He married Anne of Moulsford in 1460, in Moulsford, Berkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died after 1459, in Truro, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1440–Aft 1459":"1440–pärast 1459","1440–1459":"1440–1459","–Female":"Surnud","1460–Female":"1460–Surnud","1400–1439":"1400–1439","1405–1439":"1405–1439","1459":"1459","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","after 1439":"pärast 1439","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","Aft 1459":"pärast 1459","1439":"1439","1405":"1405","Moulsford, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Moulsford, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Truro, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Truro, Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Moulsford, Berkshire, England":"Moulsford, Berkshire, England"},"fi":{"1440–Aft 1459":"1440–1459 jälkeen","1440–1459":"1440–1459","–Female":"Kuollut","1460–Female":"1460–Kuollut","1400–1439":"1400–1439","1405–1439":"1405–1439","1459":"1459","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","after 1439":"1439 jälkeen","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","Aft 1459":"1459 jälkeen","1439":"1439","1405":"1405","Moulsford, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Moulsford, Berkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Truro, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Truro, Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Moulsford, Berkshire, England":"Moulsford, Berkshire, England"},"fr":{"1440–Aft 1459":"1440–après 1459","1440–1459":"1440–1459","–Female":"Décédée","1460–Female":"1460–Décédée","1400–1439":"1400